---
name: Fast Dialog Pipeline (Sync.so Multi-Pass Chain, v5)
description: compose-dialog-segments now dispatches N sequential Sync.so calls (one per speaker, each chained on the previous pass's output) instead of one segments[]+ASD call (which crashes lipsync-2-pro). Webhook chains via {advance: true}; per-pass payload uses single audio + single-coord ASD, NO segments[]. State stores passes[] + current_pass + total_passes. Single-speaker scenes still run as one pass.
type: feature
---

Engine: `engine_override = 'sync-segments'` (parallel to legacy `'cinematic-sync'`).

**Why multi-pass:** Sync.so `lipsync-2-pro` crashes (`An unknown error occurred`) when `segments[]` + `options.active_speaker_detection` are sent together. Dropping ASD makes the call complete but Sync.so picks audio→face auto-mapping and routinely swaps speakers. The only stable multi-speaker pattern is v4's: one call per speaker with single-coord ASD, chained.

**Per-pass payload (no segments[]):**
```json
{
  "model": "lipsync-2-pro",
  "input": [
    { "type": "video", "url": "<prev pass output OR master plate>" },
    { "type": "audio", "url": "<speaker.track_url with silence between turns>" }
  ],
  "options": {
    "active_speaker_detection": {
      "auto_detect": false,
      "frame_number": <mid of first turn>,
      "coordinates": [x, y]
    }
  },
  "webhookUrl": "..."
}
```

**State model (`dialog_shots`):**
```ts
{
  version: 5, engine: "sync-segments", status: "rendering"|"done"|"failed",
  multi_pass: boolean, passes: PassState[],
  current_pass: number, total_passes: number,
  sync_job_id: string,         // CURRENT pass's job id (for webhook match)
  source_clip_url, total_sec, cost_credits, refunded,
  first_started_at, started_at, retry_count,
  final_url?: string,          // set only on last pass COMPLETED
}
```

**Webhook flow (sync-so-webhook v5 branch):**
- COMPLETED + more passes remain → mark pass done, increment `current_pass`, fire-and-forget `compose-dialog-segments {scene_id, advance: true}`.
- COMPLETED + last pass → re-host MP4 to ai-videos, set `clip_url`, `lip_sync_applied_at`, `twoshot_stage='complete'`.
- FAILED/transient + retry budget → re-dispatch same pass via `{scene_id, retry: true}`.
- FAILED/non-retryable → idempotent refund + `lip_sync_status='failed'`.

**Requirements:** every speaker MUST have `track_url` (compose-twoshot-audio output). Missing → 422 + refund + clear error.

**Cost:** still `ceil(totalSec) * 9` credits charged ONCE upfront. All passes share the same budget (Sync.so bills per-pass internally, our user-facing price stays flat). `cost_credits` preserved across `retry=true` and `advance=true` dispatches.

**Progress bar (`usePipelineProgress.ts`):** when lipsync is terminal (done/failed) AND no master-render is running, `runSoftPercent` stops ramping toward `RUN_NOMINAL_SECONDS` and locks to `phaseOverall` (sum of weighted done phases). Eliminates the "still loading after 5 min" stuck-bar bug.

**Affected files:**
- `supabase/functions/compose-dialog-segments/index.ts` (multi-pass dispatch + advance branch)
- `supabase/functions/sync-so-webhook/index.ts` (advance vs finalize logic)
- `src/hooks/usePipelineProgress.ts` (waitingForExport cap)

**May 30 2026 — sync_mode fix:** Per-pass payload now explicitly sets `options.sync_mode: "cut_off"`. Without it Sync.so's `lipsync-2-pro` default trimmed output to the shorter input, so multi-pass chains ended after the first speaker's last turn (3rd sentence cut off). Per-speaker tracks from compose-twoshot-audio are silence-padded to scene duration, so cut_off + matching lengths now yields a full-length output. Dispatch also logs `audio_approx_sec` vs `expected_total_sec` and persists `length_mismatch` in `syncso_dispatch_log.meta` for debugging.

**May 30 2026 — progress-bar stuck fix:** Final pass now additionally writes `clip_status: "ready"` (was only `clip_url`+`lip_sync_status='applied'`). For dialog/cinematic-sync scenes the master plate is generated inside the edge function and the scene stays in `clip_status='generating'` for the whole Sync.so chain — without this flip the Composer's `usePipelineProgress.clipsReal` keeps reporting `running=true` and the global pipeline bar gets stuck at ~40 % forever even though lipsync visibly finished. `usePipelineProgress.ts.clipsReal` also got a belt-and-suspenders `isReadyOrLipsynced` helper that treats `clip_url + lip_sync_status='applied'` (or `twoshot_stage in ('complete','done')`) as ready, so older rows + future providers that forget to flip `clip_status` don't re-introduce the bug.

**May 30 2026 — Sync.so unknown-error hardening:** HappyHorse remains a valid Lip-Sync source; opaque Sync.so `provider_unknown_error` is now handled inside the Sync.so pass chain, not by blaming the source model. `compose-dialog-segments` writes a per-pass `diagnostic_id`, logs pass/model/variant/input/audio/VAD/length/coords diagnostics, validates real WAV bytes before dispatch, clamps face coordinates, and sends the diagnostic id via webhook URL. `sync-so-webhook` persists the failed pass payload + input summary and retries through a bounded fallback ladder: `coords-pro` → `auto-pro` → `auto-standard` (`lipsync-2`) before idempotent refund. Progress UI labels Sync.so concurrency as `Slots x/3` so it is not confused with pass count.

**Jun 1 2026 — NO cross-pass variant learning:** Removed the "Stage H scene-wide variant learning" block in `compose-dialog-segments`. Each pass MUST start at `coords-pro` because each pass targets a different face with its own validated coords. Inheriting `auto-pro` from a sibling pass (because pass 0 had to retry through the fallback ladder) caused the payload to drop the explicit `coordinates` field and switch to `auto_detect: true`; on the chained input video the auto-detector then re-targets speaker 0 (already animated from pass 0) and speakers 2 and 3 stay completely frozen. The per-pass retry ladder (coords-pro → auto-pro → auto-standard) still runs inside `sync-so-webhook` on actual provider failures for that specific pass only.

**Jun 1 2026 — Re-host intermediate pass outputs:** `sync-so-webhook` now re-hosts EVERY pass output (not just the last) to `ai-videos/composer/<uid>/<sceneId>-lipsync-pass-<n>.mp4` before persisting `passes[i].output_url` and dispatching the next pass. Without this, passes 2+ received the raw `api.sync.so/v2/generations/<id>/result?token=…` redirect URL as `input.url`, which Sync.so rejects in `coords-pro` mode with `provider_unknown_error`. The fallback ladder then forced each pass onto `auto-pro` (coords dropped, auto_detect=true), and the auto-detector latched onto speaker 0's already-animated mouth — speakers 2 and 3 stayed completely frozen. Re-host failure is a soft fallback (log + keep Sync.so URL), so the chain never blocks on a transient storage error. Single-speaker scenes are unaffected (only the existing last-pass re-host runs).

**Jun 2 2026 — Plate-dim probe + no-auto fallback for multi-speaker:** Two-part fix for the "voiceover but no lips move at all" symptom in 3-speaker scenes.
1. `_shared/twoshot-face-map.ts` now exports `probeMp4Dims(url)` (pure-TS ISO BMFF box walker reading the first ~768 KiB) that returns the visual track's pixel `{width,height}` from the first non-zero `tkhd`. `compose-dialog-segments` probes the actual master plate (Hailuo i2v output) before face resolution and passes the result as `videoDims` to `pickSpeakerCoordinates` so anchor-space coords get scaled into plate-space. Without this the Nano-Banana anchor's resolution was used as the coordinate basis, but the Hailuo plate can have different aspect/crop → coords landed off-face → Sync.so rejected `coords-pro` with `provider_unknown_error`. Probed dims are persisted to `dialog_shots.video_width`/`video_height` (also consumed by `render-sync-segments-audio-mux` for the Lambda canvas).
2. `sync-so-webhook` now BLOCKS the `auto-pro` / `auto-standard` rungs of the retry ladder when `passes.length >= 2`. The auto-* variants set `auto_detect: true` and drop the explicit coordinates; on wide group shots Sync.so's auto-detector either targets the wrong face OR silently passes the input through unchanged (= no lip movement at all). Both modes look like a "successful" pass in the DB but produce a video where speakers 2+ are frozen. Multi-speaker scenes now fall through to the idempotent-refund path after `coords-pro` exhausts its retry budget, surfacing a clear `lip_sync_status='failed'` + `clip_error` for the user instead of a silent broken video. Single-speaker scenes keep the full `coords-pro → auto-pro → auto-standard` ladder (auto is safe with only 1 face in frame).
3. Dispatch log line now includes `anchor=WxH plate=WxH` so coordinate-space mismatches are visible at a glance.
